column23: 4020 N 20th St Suite 219, Phoenix, AZ 85016, United States
column28:
FoodStory Brands (FSB) is a team of food-obsessed experts in branding, prime sourcing, product development and logistics.   We specialize in product innovation and speed-to-market solutions across all food and beverage categories in the nation’s leading food retailers.

FSB is passionate about finding and developing new food and beverage products with compelling brand ideas that bring the best food stories to life from real people and places.  We search around the world and in our own backyard to uncover foods and flavors from culinary pioneers, up-and-coming food entrepreneurs, and longtime favorite brands connected to inspiring new food ideas.

Our mission is simply to bring authentic food stories to America’s table every day!  Some of our brands include:

- Fresh Cravings (www.fresh-cravings.com) - a line of refrigerated salsa that was founded on freshness.  Our salsa doesn’t belong on a shelf in the chip aisle; instead, you can find our salsas where other natural products are located... in the Produce section.  Made with hand-picked, vine-ripened tomatoes, fresh jalapenos and earthy spices, Fresh Cravings salsa is a snack you can feel good about indulging in.  Go ahead… Crave On!

- Cocktail Artist (www.cocktail-artist.com) - a line of premium bar ingredients and mixes developed by Award-Winning Mixologists.  The products contain no high fructose corn syrup and no artificial flavors or colors, and set a new standard for quality, authenticity and convenience.  Cocktail Artist makes it easy for the home bartender to mix high quality, craft cocktails for their friends and family.  The glass is your canvas, mix it like you mean it!

- Sweet Offerings Bake Shop (www.sweetofferings.com) - takes pleasure in creating unique indulgences featuring flavors beloved by people around the world, including Biscoff Cookies and Cold Stone Creamery.

column23: 1 Off Jalan Yew Fraser Business Park, Kuala Lumpur, AZ 55100, Malaysia
column28:
Fraser & Neave Holdings Bhd (F&NHB) is one of Malaysia’s diversified blue chip companies with an annual turnover in excess of RM4 billion from its core business in manufacturing, sales and marketing of beverages and dairy products. With a rich heritage over 135 years, its portfolio of brands enjoy market leadership in many categories. 

Founded in 1883 by John Fraser and David Chalmers Neave, from whom the instantly recognisable initials ‘F&N’ are derived, F&N is today an iconic household brand that is closely integrated into the nation’s fabric. F&N enjoys a special place in the hearts of Malaysians, one that is trusted by generations while fulfilling its promise of ‘Pure Enjoyment, Pure Goodness’ through its wide portfolio of well-loved brands and products.

F&NHB has over 2,500 employees and is Malaysia's top 100 leading graduate employers. F&NHB operates in Malaysia, Brunei, Thailand and Indochina, and is a subsidiary of Fraser and Neave, Limited, a company listed on the Singapore Stock Exchange.  Today, F&N has spread its export reach to more than 60 countries worldwide.

column23: 1686 N Higley Rd Ste 105, Gilbert, AZ 85206, United States
column28:
Genuine Fresche. Acai bowls are the latest craze in healthy eating. Fresche is a quick serve restaurant that specializes in blended frozen fruit bowls, topped with fresh fruit, granola and other super-food add-ins. We don't add ice so the consistency is thick and smooth. (Like a smoothie in a bowl with toppings). Our focus is serving whole, healthy, great tasting food. Fresche is a place that your body can trust, and your taste buds will demand. Fresche acai bowls are lower in sugar, dairy free, with gluten free options.

Vegan, Vegetarian, Paleo and Diabetic friendly. Just let us know what your preference is.   

Fresche matches up well with the growing trend of consumers who are demanding truly healthy food options. Many restaurants claim to have healthy menu items, when in reality they are not.  Thrive! is a place that leaves you feeling good about what you have fueled your body with.  

If you are looking for acai bowls in Tempe, Mesa, Scottsdale or Phoenix, it is worth the drive!

Because of our passion for natural wellness we have researched and found high quality, whole food supplements and proteins that we are excited to offer here at Fresche.

column28:
Maui Wowi Hawaiian is the only franchise that offers authentic, natural Hawaiian products, fresh-fruit smoothies, blended Hawaiian coffee beverages and lifestyle merchandise. Ditch the button down for a Hawaiian shirt, it's time to take control!

With over 450 franchised units throughout the United States and in seven countries, Maui Wowi is a leader in non-traditional venues such as sports stadiums, arenas, racetracks and more. From event carts, mall kiosks, and stand-alone retail locations, there is a business model to fit any lifestyle. 

The smoothies are all-natural, gluten free, fat-free, and kosher certified; made using premium quality ingredients and freshly blended. Our coffees come from the premier coffee growing region on the Hawaiian Islands, including the Kona District of the Big Island of Hawaii. They are roasted fresh and brewed to perfection!

Ranked on Entrepreneur's Franchise 500 and as a Low-Cost Franchise, Maui Wowi continues to seek out qualified individuals who are interested in the opportunity to take control of their destiny and become their own boss as a franchise business owner.

column23: 1471 W Commerce Court, Tucson, AZ 85746, United States
column28:
Our Mission:
Merit Foods aims to be the best local independent family owned full-line food Distribution Company serving Southern Arizona. As an alternative to the large national broad-line distributors, we aim to enhance your business through strong partnerships resulting in mutual growth. 

Our Vision:
As a company we are dedicated to combining valuable customer service with superior products.  We are committed to providing the highest quality inspected custom-cut meats, fresh produce, and groceries. To welcome will-call orders to the public at our new state-of-the-art warehouse in Tucson, Arizona.

Core Values:
Dedication – We believe in going the extra mile for our customers.

Integrity– Our team closely monitors marketplace conditions and works closely with vendor partners, keeping prices as competitive and fair as possible

Dependability – In many areas, we offer prompt delivery with low minimums.

Allegiance – For our client Partners, we offer complimentary marketing and design materials to help expand and grow your business. For our supplier associates, we offer marketing programs that allow for optimum exposure.

Thinking Local:
Supporting our local community is an extremely high priority to us. We are a member of Arizona Local First and a preferred purveyor of the Tucson Originals. Alongside these organizations we strive to create a stronger and more vibrant economy for Arizonans.

column23: 4308 E Main St, Mesa, AZ 85205, United States
column28: Midwestern Meats is a family owned Arizona business specializing in cornfed beef shipped in directly from Iowa. The company was founded by expert meat cutter,  Roger McConnell, who began the company in 1991 at the age of 45. At a time where people his age was eyeing retirement, Roger decided to go for his dream, cashed in his retirement savings to  open up Midwestern Meats in a 2000 square foot store on Main Street in Mesa, Arizona. He had only one other employee and for the first 3 years, worked 18-hour days doing everything from butchering to helping customers to mopping the shop floors. His wife Sally, a homemaker for most of their marriage, took her first day job to help pay the bills, and spent nights doing the bookkeeping for the store. For the next 20 years, Midwestern Meats has grown to 50 employees, a bakery and a restuarant located in a 15,000 square foot location. It also sells its products online under www.megameatstore.com and has even expanded its line of foods through its newest division, Midwestern Fitness. Although Roger is no longer involved in the day to day aspects of the business, his vision and philosophy remains part of the company under the leadership of his son, Rod McConnell.

column23: 7 South Mikes Pike Street, Flagstaff, AZ 86001, United States
column28:
Driving on a dark stretch of two lane road, founders Michael and Alissa Marquess were pondering how to better live their creed of ‘finding joy in the adventure’.  They decided to create a brewery that brought together their passions of craft beer, travel, Arizona and the enjoyment of life.

   Mother Road hand crafts each of our beers along a lost portion of Route 66 in a 1920s era industrial laundry building with a small staff.  We found craft beer, where does your road lead?

   We are distributed state-wide in Arizona by Hensley Beverage Company of Phoenix and Romer Beverage Company in Kingman.  Premier Distributing Company wholesales Mother Road across the state of New Mexico.

column23: 853 S Main St, Cottonwood, AZ 86326, United States
column28:
Mount Hope is a family owned and operated business that has been offering the very finest in top quality foods and customer service for more than 30 years. We have built up our reputation by providing the best nuts, dried fruits, spices, beans, rices, grains, mushrooms, chilies, extracts and specialty products available. The only thing better than our service and selection is our prices.

Since we run a smaller and more specialized operation than major food distributors, we’re able to turn over our stock much more quickly, which means fresher inventory when it is shipped to you. We offer free UPS ground delivery to wholesale customers, low commercial minimums, and we will ship your order the same day it is placed. Our customers include restaurants, resorts, bakeries, culinary schools, caterers, and food manufacturers all over the US. They love doing business with us and we know you will too!

column28:
Next Phase Enterprises (NPE) is a full-service Sales, Marketing and Logistics team of professionals with more than 500 years of combined industry experience.  NPE serves the Mass Merchandise, Club, and Grocery channels which include Walmart, Sam’s Club, Costco, BJ’s and Kroger.  Since the company was founded in 1995, it has grown from 2 clients and $4 Million in annual retail sales to 45 clients and more than $500 Million in sales.  The company is headquartered in Phoenix, AZ and has regional sales offices throughout the country.

NPE’s success and growth is driven by its five core values, which are:  We Are a Family Company; We Have Mutual Trust & Respect for Each Other; We Show a Spirit of Service to Our Partners, Our Community, and Each Other; We Commit to a Work/Life Balance; and We Focus on Innovation.

column23: 5141 N 40th St # 300 Suite 300, Phoenix, AZ, United States
column28:
The seeds of Oregano go all the way back to the mid 1900’s when Siegfried, a German chef, left home in Cologne and traveled around Europe is in search of flavours. When Siegfried reached Liguria in the North West coast of Italy, he discovered a cuisine that captured his palate and Mirella, who captured his heart and eventually became his wife. Maurizio was born soon after.  Their family run restaurant served food for the soul.

Maurizio did not turn out to be a Chef but he could explain flavours like no other.  It was a chance meeting with two brothers that the flavours Maurizio knew as a child would be replicated. Tony had a Hotel Management Degree from Switzerland & Australia and George, a business man who had the ability to transform these gifts to a business model with passion.

The three of them connected well. Tony with his creative flair and passion towards cooking and was able to replicate flavours from Liguria and all of them were convinced that this dining experience was to be rolled out to the world. They decided to open a small restaurant in Dubai serving Ligurian inspired cuisine.  The first Oregano restaurant ever!

With the passion becoming contagious, today Oregano boasts 10 restaurants in Dubai and Abu Dhabi serving Ligurian inspired dishes prepared with flavour for all Oregano guests to experience and enjoy. Oregano is now growing the brand internationally with the franchise model and privately owned outlets and one day will open an outlet in Liguria where the journey actually started.

column23: 8 S San Marcos Pl, Chandler, AZ, United States
column28:
About SanTan Brewery, Distillery + Eatery
In 2007, SanTan Brewing Company opened the doors of our original brewpub, located in the heart of Historic Downtown Chandler. Founder and Brewmaster Anthony Canecchia’s mission of pairing craft beer with craft food, to inspire great conversation and good times, still stands true today for Arizona’s
largest craft brewery.

Launched in May 2018, SanTan Distilling uses only 100% malted American barley for our award-winning handcrafted whiskey + vodkas. Distilled with the use of our custom-built artisan pot still in small batches, SanTan believes our spirits represent the very best from the American West.

In addition to producing quality craft beverages, SanTan also features two popular neighborhood brewpubs located in Historic Downtown Chandler and Uptown Phoenix. Visit SanTanBrewing.com for more information.

column5: Vice President of Business Development and Sales
column23: 2510 W Geneva Dr, Tempe, AZ 85282, United States
column28:
The only Single Italian Brand distributor present in America, supplying a true authentic taste of Italy.

At times, it is a double-edged sword to be the only American company  applying the model of a single band food distributor when working with  numerous partners, while maintaining our high standards from inception  to delivery, restaurant to restaurant.
On one hand, we can boast the superior quality and dedication to  research and development on all levels of our company, and on the other,  we cannot provide our clients with excuses as to where there  potentially be defects or inconsistencies in our product. We are our own  manufactures.
This involves extreme attention and a lot of “behind the scenes” work  from the quality control team of Sogno Toscano. The company invests  heavily in research and follows the production from A to Z. Throughout  the year, we scour each unique region to select Italy’s best products.  This is in valuable addition to what we cultivate at our estate in  Bolgheri, Tuscany.
For each Sogno Toscano product, we perform rigorous laboratory  testing, sampling, and tasting by aware winning chefs. We develop the  spec sheets, packaging, and lot selection as well as monitor the  loading, withdrawal, and container closure with our safety seal.
All of our products are GMO-free and our suppliers are certified to  distribute by the Food & Drug Administration (FDA) regulations.
We pay special attention, care, and precision to each shipment  through a system of checks. Our commitment to quality combines the  wholesomeness of nature with the most advanced technology in production.
This is the secret to our success.
Pietro Brembilla
 
President

column23: 2510 W Geneva Dr, Tempe, AZ 85282, United States
column28:
The only Single Italian Brand distributor present in America, supplying a true authentic taste of Italy.

At times, it is a double-edged sword to be the only American company  applying the model of a single band food distributor when working with  numerous partners, while maintaining our high standards from inception  to delivery, restaurant to restaurant.
On one hand, we can boast the superior quality and dedication to  research and development on all levels of our company, and on the other,  we cannot provide our clients with excuses as to where there  potentially be defects or inconsistencies in our product. We are our own  manufactures.
This involves extreme attention and a lot of “behind the scenes” work  from the quality control team of Sogno Toscano. The company invests  heavily in research and follows the production from A to Z. Throughout  the year, we scour each unique region to select Italy’s best products.  This is in valuable addition to what we cultivate at our estate in  Bolgheri, Tuscany.
For each Sogno Toscano product, we perform rigorous laboratory  testing, sampling, and tasting by aware winning chefs. We develop the  spec sheets, packaging, and lot selection as well as monitor the  loading, withdrawal, and container closure with our safety seal.
All of our products are GMO-free and our suppliers are certified to  distribute by the Food & Drug Administration (FDA) regulations.
We pay special attention, care, and precision to each shipment  through a system of checks. Our commitment to quality combines the  wholesomeness of nature with the most advanced technology in production.
This is the secret to our success.
Pietro Brembilla
 
President

column23: 2831 N 31st Ave, Phoenix, AZ, United States
column28:
St. Mary's Food Bank is the the largest Arizona-based non-profit distributing food to more than 400 partner agencies throughout most of Arizona. With 180 full-time team members, St. Mary's has annual revenues in excess of $150M. St. Mary's is the world's original food bank and is celebrating its 50th year in 2017.  St. Mary's is recognized as the very first food bank to inspire the practice of gathering and sharing food worldwide.

Last year St. Mary's fleet of 40 semi and straight trucks drove more than one million miles.  More than 90 million pounds of food was distributed including 1M+ meals to children through our Kids Cafe program.

St. Mary's Food Bank touches countless lives by providing healthy food to those in need.

column23: 3200 S 7th St, Flagstaff, AZ, United States
column28: Stern Produce has proudly served the Arizona community for four generations, since 1917. For 100 years, our mission has remained the same – “to deliver a first-class customer experience as we supply the freshest, fruits, vegetables specialty food products, and meats.” This mission has served us well and will continue as our foundation as we look toward the next 100 years. We will be implementing fresh new ideas in order to serve our customers and community better. We believe the success of our business is embedded in the overall strength and resiliency of our society, the well-being of our employees, and the relationships that we weave within our local community. This includes our commitment to support Arizona agriculture and food production through meaningful partnerships.

column23: 2212 E Williams Field Rd, Gilbert, AZ 85297, United States
column28:
Thirsty Lion aims to revolutionize the gastropub business by combining the traditional values of European and American pubs, creating a gathering place where friends and family can come together to celebrate life, enjoy great food, craft beers, signature cocktails, wines, music and sports.

By day, Thirsty Lion is a unique location for a business lunch or a great spot to enjoy drinks. At dinnertime, it’s a comfortable setting for friends and family to dine, catch the game and have a beer. And for night owls, it’s an entertaining venue for an evening out with friends to enjoy great music videos, a late night menu, and quality cocktails.  

Thirsty Lion’s culinary commitment is to provide an eclectic variety of multi-cultural cuisines with an emphasis on local ingredients, bold flavors and scratch recipes. The fresh sheet focuses on the changing seasons with unique ingredients including fresh seafood, quality meats, and local vegetables & fruits.  Thirsty Lion is well known for featuring a diverse variety of 52 craft, import and domestic beers on draft as well as signature cocktails and regional wines.

Arizona's premiere late-night cookie and ice cream delivery service. Now serving Phoenix, Scottsdale, and Tempe Thursday through Sunday 7 p.m. to 4 a.m.

Totally Baked Cookie Co. was started by a student that found herself turning to her peers during a late night study session at the library asking "You know what would be really great right now? Cookies. Delivered."​

Everyone loves melt-in-your-mouth cookies. But what could make it better? Having them delivered. So don't kill the vibe by having to drive. We are the catchall cure for even the most serious munchies. 

Count on us to satisfy your late night cravings for whatever keeps you up at night.

column28:
Founded in 1998 by Kathryn Petty, White Lion Tea offers a collection of rare and beautiful teas from the world’s finest gardens. We provide a wide range of specialty tea products to service the hospitality industry; hotels and resorts, restaurants, spas, and coffee and tea shops. Elegantly packaged gifts, retail items, and amenities support the brand and drive profit. Key distributors include 
Sysco Foods and Avendra-approved Atlanta Foods International and Universal Companies. 

White Lion is a leading expert in operations and implementation of tea service in the hospitality segment. We are known for our impressive and highly styled presentation boxes and service style accessories. We excel in 
customization and small run private label programs that include marketing materials designed to drive profit. We provide training materials to support operations, procedures, and best practices. We can create a “boutique feel” yet execute at a national scale. We are known innovators, offering proprietary products such as Honey Pearls, an all natural crystallized honey.
